## Pass Args to Commands

When you have an [inferred task](/docs/concepts/inferred-tasks) (or an explicitly defined task using the [`nx:run-commands` executor](/docs/guides/tasks--caching/run-commands-executor#2-update)) running a command, there'll come a time when you'll need to pass args to the underlying command being run. This recipe explains how you can achieve that.

## Example project and tasks

For this recipe we'll use a project with the following `project.json` file:

```json
// apps/my-app/project.json
{
  "sourceRoot": "apps/my-app/src",
  "projectType": "application",
  "targets": {}
}
```

And the following [final configuration](/docs/reference/project-configuration):

```json
{
  "project": {
    "name": "my-app",
    "type": "app",
    "data": {
      "name": "my-app",
      "root": "apps/my-app",
      "sourceRoot": "apps/my-app/src",
      "projectType": "application",
      "targets": {
